entries.Name: KidSTART Group Helpers (Jul - Dec 2022)
entries.Description:
We are looking for volunteers to assist us in our weekly playgroup sessions for children between 1-3 years old (Total: 20 Sessions) every Wednesday in Woodlands!

 

Commitment Period: Volunteers need to attend a minimum of 5 consecutive sessions. Even better if you can attend all 20 sessions! 😊

 

Address: Youth Guidance Outreach Services – Woodlands Centre at Blk 804 Woodlands St 81, #01-37, S730804

Session day/timing: Wednesdays, 2.30pm to 6.30pm

 

Sessions’ Schedule: (To attend at least 5 consecutive sessions below)

  1. Wed 20 Jul
  2. Wed 27 Jul
  3. Wed 3 Aug
  4. Wed 10 Aug
  5. Wed 17 Aug
  6. Wed 24 Aug
  7. Wed 31 Aug
  8. Wed 14 Sep
  9. Wed 21 Sep
  10. Wed 28 Sep
  11. Wed 5 Oct
  12. Wed 12 oct
  13. Wed 19 Oct
  14. Wed 26 Oct
  15. Wed 2 Nov
  16. Wed 9 Nov
  17. Wed 16 Nov
  18. Wed 23 Nov
  19. Wed 30 Nov
  20. Wed 7 Dec

Scope of support required for each session:

  • Help Facilitators in preparing the environment
  • Welcome parents and health screening (if necessary)
  • Engage children at the playmats while their parents are at the briefing session with the Facilitators (about 20 to 30 minutes)
  • Pack up and sanitizing of the toys and learning materials after each session
  • Join in shared reading time and circle time
  • Facilitating mealtime (i.e., giving out Bento sets) and goodbye to families

entries.Name: Youth Corps Community Fair 2022
entries.Description:
“I want to try out volunteering but I don’t know where to go…” 

“I want to know more about different causes but I don’t know who to approach…” 

“I want to learn new skills but I don’t know where to start…”

 

 

If you have ever had these thoughts in mind - come and visit us at The Red Box for our Youth Corps Community Fair! Happening at the end of July, Youth Corps Community Fair is where you can discover and learn about opportunities to serve with various causes or communities championing for various causes ranging from children and youth, seniors, special needs, mental health and more!

 

Small steps can lead to big changes; come visit us and you might just be part of a rallying force to serve the community 🙌

 

Scroll down to read more! See you there!

 

Note: 

  • This is an event opportunity that serves as a platform for youth communities (ground-up initiatives, projects, groups) to connect with others to enrich the local youth volunteering scene. No community service is involved, hence service hours will not be awarded.

  • Sign ups for the activities will be updated at a later date

entries.Name: Removal of invasive climbers @Telok Blangah Hill Park
entries.NameTooltip: Removal of invasive climbers @Telok Blangah Hill Park
entries.Description:
In celebration of National Day, #DoingGood campaign, NParks is organising an Invasive Species Management activity at Telok Blangah Hill Park to encourage the community to come together and care for our environment.

Invasive species pose a threat to biodiversity. They compete for space, light, water and nutrients with other native species. You can often find them smothering our native trees in the park. By removing these invasive species, you are protecting the natural ecosystem and creating a better home for our local flora and fauna.

 

Come and have a hands-on session to learn what are the invasive climbers that are not welcomed in our forest.

entries.Name: Youth Corps Leaders Programme - Cohort 29 [YCLP]
entries.Description:
Interested to step up as a volunteer leader to serve the community and lead community initiatives? The Youth Corps Leaders Programme – Project Track is a leadership development programme that offers the following opportunities for you!  

  • Develop community leadership skills through training, mentoring and implementation of a sustainable service-learning project
    • Gain insight into national issues and challenges, and the individual’s role in shaping Singapore
    • Be empowered to lead, advocate, and take action on community issues that you are passionate about
    • Learn to assess community needs and manage partnerships
    • Lead self and build high performing teams

      • Applications for the Youth Corps Leaders Programme is now open! Register now at https://go.gov.sg/yclp29-vsg. More details are in the edm below.

entries.Name: YMCA Youth Club (Y BookStop) [YCLP]
entries.Description:
This opportunity is a youth-led initiative part of Youth Corps Leaders Programme.

In conjunction with YMCA, Team Genesis is looking for Volunteers to support and work towards the social cause of improving the well being of the special needs community and help them integrate better into society. 

Known as the YMCA Youth Club, the club will allow special needs clients to get together and have a home-like environment; with a diverse range of programs aimed at enabling special need clients with new employable skills and have fun at the same time. 

Y BookStop is a fundraising book sale event aimed to raise funds to support the new YMCA Youth Club programmes for clients with special needs.

  • Note: It is a requirement by YMCA for volunteers to be 18 years old this year. Therefore, volunteers who are still 17 years old but turning 18 this year may continue to apply for the opportunity.

entries.Name: Re:ground@Dungeon - The Reflection Series: A Little Kindness
entries.NameTooltip: Re:ground@Dungeon - The Reflection Series: A Little Kindness
entries.Description:
Come and find us at our themed activity nights to practice self-care through activities based on a specific theme! 

In the next part of The Reflection Series, we explore kindness to self and others in A Little Kindness ✨. 

Be the start of the ripple effect by spreading a little kindness wherever and whenever you can. Join us as we take these precious few hours to think about the kindness people gave us and how we can channel this further on❤️🌈. 

Look forward to fun activities like painting your own unique kindness pebble, penning down your thoughts using our journaling prompts and self-exploration cards, adding kindness messages our chalk wall and more!


*Other activities are still available at Re:ground @ Dungeon.

About Re:ground @ Dungeon

Re:ground @ Dungeon is a space where you can seek respite and ground yourself through activities that support in regulating your mental well-being.

 

Note: This is an event opportunity that aims to raise social awareness. No community service is involved, hence service hours will not be awarded.
